        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I switch AI website builders later?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Technically yes, but it's painful and time-consuming. Most AI builders don't export clean HTML/CSS code - you're locked into their hosting. To switch: export your text and images manually, choose a new builder, rebuild from scratch, reconnect your domain. Migration typically takes 4-10 hours depending on site complexity. The lock-in is real. Choose carefully because switching means essentially rebuilding. Some builders are easier to leave than others (Framer exports React code, Webflow exports HTML/CSS). Most (Durable, Mixo, Squarespace) don't export at all. Think long-term: if you might need to export later, choose a builder that allows it."
        }
